cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DC

The paper deals with game theory and resource allocation in an IoT system, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory), as the paper explicitly uses game theory to model the problem. The second likely category is cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with resource allocation in an IoT system. The third likely category is cs.SY (Computer Science - Systems and Control), as the paper deals with distributed resource allocation. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a novel game-theoretic approach based on cognitive hierarchy theory. The fifth likely category is cs.DC (Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with distributed resource allocation in an IoT system.
